                          <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-1"> I often get emails from autoimmune disease sufferers saying, &quot;I'd like to try doing what you did, but how can you give up meat, cheese and ice cream?!&quot; My answer is: Why would you choose those foods over your health? The truth is, people use the phrase &quot;giving up&quot; because they think they're making a sacrfice. I'm not sacrificing anything because I love the foods I eat and I don't miss anything from the way I used to eat. I get the pleasure of eating delicious food and being healthy to boot. I recently got a pressure cooker which revolutionized our vegetarian eating. <a href="http://www.vegsource.com/articles2/pressure_cookers.htm" target="_blank">Click here</a> to read an article I wrote on it.</font></p>                      </td>
